Samson Folarin Chaos broke out on the Ikeja Along, Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway, after motorcycle riders and personnel of the Lagos State Task Force clashed. In viral video, scores of riders are seen chasing the security operatives while spitting out a stream of expletives as the task force officers retreated to their operational vehicles which zoomed off immediately. It is the second day of the fight between the riders and the government officers. READ ALSO: Groups hit FG over claim bandits have been degraded On Tuesday, the task force officers seized over 70 motorcycles around Second Rainbow, FESTAC Town over infraction of traffic laws, which resulted in a clash between them and the okada riders. Details later…